I believe you may have already found a solution, but I&#39;m providing an answer in case others are facing a similar issue.

The error you encountered seems to be related to how you are setting the node addresses. Starting from Redisson version 2.7.X, you need to use the redis:// protocol in the node addresses. However, for versions before 2.7.X, you should not use the redis:// protocol.

To fix the issue, please try the following:

**For Redisson versions 2.7.X and above:**

    Config config = new Config();
    config.useClusterServers()
    .addNodeAddress(&quot;redis://localhost:6001&quot;, &quot;redis://localhost:6001&quot;);
    RedissonClient redisson = Redisson.create(config);


**For Redisson versions before 2.7.X:**

    Config config = new Config();
    config.useClusterServers()
    .addNodeAddress(&quot;localhost:6001&quot;, &quot;localhost:6002&quot;);
    RedissonClient redisson = Redisson.create(config);


Make sure to replace the port numbers and hostnames with the appropriate values for your Redis cluster configuration.

I hope this helps!

