I don&#39;t believe you&#39;ll be able to use the `@Timed` annotation to accomplish what you&#39;re doing, but you can manually time the method and do what you want.  Here is an example:

```
.
.
.
@Autowired MeterRegistry meterRegistry;
.
.
.
public Info getInfo(@PathVariable(&quot;id&quot;) String id) {
    final Sample sample = Timer.start(meterRegistry);
    
    final Info info = Info.getById(id);

    sample.stop(Timer.builder(&quot;timed&quot;)
                     .tag(&quot;account&quot;, Account.getById(id)
                     .register(meterRegistry));
    return info;
}
```

Now it&#39;s possible to do it using annotation called [@MeterTag][1]

So for example you can do it like this:

    @Timed
    public Info getInfo(@MeterTag(&quot;id&quot;) @PathVariable(&quot;id&quot;) String id) {
        return Info.getById(id);
    }

  [1]: https://github.com/micrometer-metrics/micrometer/pull/3727

